<!-- javax.baja.platform.security.PlatformSecurityConfigManager.isPlatformAccountValid() -->
<method name="isPlatformAccountValid"  public="true" abstract="true">
<description>
Verifies that the current Platform account is not the default Platform account.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; If the current Platform Account set to the default Platform Account, return FALSE.&#xa; If the Platform Account is set to any other account, return TRUE.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa;&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; No parameters are required.
</description>
<tag name="@since">Niagara 4.1</tag>
<return>
<type class="boolean"/>
</return>
</method>

<!-- javax.baja.platform.security.PlatformSecurityConfigManager.replacePlatformAccount(javax.baja.platform.security.BPlatformAccountChangeRequest) -->
<method name="replacePlatformAccount"  public="true" abstract="true">
<annotation><type class="java.lang.SuppressWarnings"/>
<elementValue name="value">
<annotationValue kind="array">
<elementArray>
<annotationValue kind="expr">
<expression>&#x22;DeprecatedIsStillUsed&#x22;</expression>
</annotationValue>
</elementArray>
</annotationValue>
</elementValue>
</annotation>
<annotation><type class="java.lang.Deprecated"/>
</annotation>
<description>
Set the new Platform account.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; NOTICE: Function implementation has been removed. Use addPlatformUser and removePlatformUser in&#xa; the &lt;code&gt;<see ref="javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager">javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager</see>&lt;/code&gt; interface.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; Exceptions and causes:&#xa; BajaRuntimeException:&#xa; platformAccountData is null.&#xa; One or more required components for the platformAccountData are missing.&#xa; The account credentials provided for authentication did not match an existing account.&#xa; The passphrase for the new platform account does not meet security requirements.&#xa; The platform provider is unable to verify the authentication account due to an IO error.&#xa; The platform provider is unable to create the new platform account due to an IO error&#xa; The platform provider is unable to remove the old platform account due to an IO error&#xa; A passphrase encode failed.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; The specified account information is used to create the new account, and the provided&#xa; credentials are used to a)determine if the user has the rights to modify the account information,&#xa; and b) to remove the old account.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; Parameters:&#xa; platformAccountData.authenticationUsername&#xa; The username for the current platform account.&#xa; platformAccountData.authenticationPassphrase&#xa; The passphrase for the current platform account&#xa; platformAccountData.newUsername&#xa; The username for the account to be created.&#xa; platformAccountData.newPassphrase&#xa; The passphrase for the account to be created.&#xa; platformAccountData.newComment&#xa; A comment to add to the new user account.
</description>
<tag name="@since">Niagara 4.1</tag>
<tag name="@deprecated">This function has been removed as of Niagara 4.13, as the appropriate workflow&#xa; to replace a platform account is to add a new account with &lt;code&gt;<see ref="javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager#addPlatformUser(java.lang.String, char[])">javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager#addPlatformUser</see>&lt;/code&gt;&#xa; and remove existing with &lt;code&gt;<see ref="javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager#removePlatformUser(java.lang.String)">javax.baja.platform.DaemonSecurityManager#removePlatformUser</see>&lt;/code&gt;.</tag>
<parameter name="platformAccountData">
<type class="javax.baja.platform.security.BPlatformAccountChangeRequest"/>
<description>
user name for the platform daemon&#x27;s admin
</description>
</parameter>
<return>
<type class="void"/>
</return>
</method>

